  "prompt": "Can men feel the hymen when they insert their penis into the vagina?",
  "response": "The hymen is a thin membrane that partially covers the vaginal opening in some women, but its presence, thickness, and elasticity can vary significantly from person to person. During intercourse, a man may be aware of the hymen if it is present and if it has a significant structure, but many women have a hymen that is flexible or has already stretched from activities such as tampon use, physical activity, or previous sexual experiences. \n\nIn many cases, the hymen does not create a noticeable sensation during intercourse. For some women, the first experience of penetration may result in slight discomfort or minor tearing of the hymen, which can cause some bleeding, while for others, there may be no discomfort or bleeding at all. Thus, whether a man can feel the hymen during penetration largely depends on the individual anatomy and circumstances.",
